<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>Safari Writer Export</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6;
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 2em auto;
            padding: 0 1em;
            color: #333;
        }
        pre {
            background: #f4f4f4;
            padding: 1em;
            overflow-x: auto;
        }
        blockquote {
            border-left: 5px solid #ccc;
            margin: 1.5em 10px;
            padding: 0.5em 10px;
            color: #666;
        }
        code {
            background: #f4f4f4;
            padding: 0.2em 0.4em;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
<h1>Who is Safari Writer For?</h1>

<p>Safari Writer is for anyone who appreciates the simplicity and focus of early computing:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Retro Computing Enthusiasts</strong>: Experience the feel of 8-bit word processing without the hardware limitations.</li>
  <li><strong>Distraction-Free Writers</strong>: A minimalist, text-only interface that lets you focus on your words.</li>
  <li><strong>Keyboard Power Users</strong>: Full control over your document through keyboard shortcuts and formatting markers.</li>
  <li><strong>Learners &amp; Explorers</strong>: Revisit the roots of modern word processors and see how things used to be done.</li>
</ul>

<p>Whether you&#x27;re writing a novel, a quick note, or just exploring the retro aesthetic, Safari Writer provides a unique and satisfying writing experience.</p>
</body>
</html>
